Analysts await Oracle Corporation (NYSE:ORCL) to report earnings on September, 21. They expect $0.55 earnings per share, up 12.24% or $0.06 from last year’s $0.49 per share. ORCL’s profit will be $2.26 billion for 23.02 P/E if the $0.55 EPS becomes a reality. After $0.82 actual earnings per share reported by Oracle Corporation for the previous quarter, Wall Street now forecasts -32.93% negative EPS growth. 
